answers.text: This was completely messed up. Terrible. .  I wound up paying for everything even though I was hurt at work . I recieved a letter stating that I had to respond in five days from the date the letter was SENT .  It was sent regular mail and was already to late by the time I got the notice.  I was not informed of the process until it was to late to do anything. this has been really hard on me. my eyes were burnt , it was very painfl. I had to use my vacation time and have been working overtime to pay the medical bills. Again, I was hurt at work, litterally in the same building I was treated at (UC hospital)  while working on equipment in the building, it couldnt be more clear cut. .

Very frustrating process. The left hand doesn’t know what the right hand is doing and only makes decisions based on a book or note. The bureau doctors are a joke and don’t even lay a hand or allow patients to describe or explain issues.
